4 February 2002The GCIS media briefings will be held from 11 - 15 February 2002. The briefings are traditionally held after the State of Nation Address and the second recess of parliament. This time the briefings will be held in cluster format. The ministers will outline in detail the government's programme of action for each cluster for the year to the media. The briefings will be held as follows:Venue: Rainforest Room, 120 Plein Street, Parliament, Cape Town Date: 11 - 15 February 2002The schedule is available on the GCIS web site and will be on the government web site (www.gov.za) early this week.Enquiries Sputnik Ratau Cell: 083 253 5264Harold Maloka Cell: 082 450 7304Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)